  • public class Experiment
extends java.lang.Object
    Author:

      • addMove

        public void addMove(java.lang.Integer numberOfSensors,
                    java.lang.Integer numberOfMoves,
                    java.lang.Integer currentRun)
        registers a number of moves to the number of sensors. if this is the last run, then the average of the moves is calculated. otherwise it is just added to the last value of moves.
        Parameters:
        numberOfSensors - the current number of sensors
        numberOfMoves - the number of moves taken to cover the range
        currentRun - the current run the algorithm was run with this number of sensors
